<=================================ah hod commands


use to  automate a single task on one or more managed nodes. they are quick and easy, not reusable. great for tasks you repeat rarely without writing a playbook

Why use ad hoc commands?

Use cases for ad hoc tasks
Rebooting servers
Managing files
Managing packages
Managing users and groups
Managing services
Gathering facts
Check mode
Patterns and ad-hoc commands


note : Ansible's playbooks and modules are designed to be idempotent, meaning running them multiple times will not change the system state beyond the initial configuration
 	


